sentences: Teedra Shenita Moses (born December 17, 1976) is an American R&B and soul singer.
Moses was born and raised in New Orleans, Louisiana.
She later moved to Los Angeles with her mother and three siblings after her parents separated.
Moses teamed up with producer Paul Poli and signed with the Indie Record Label, TVT Records to release her debut album Complex Simplicity in August 2004.
She was featured on and co-wrote two songs from Raphael Saadiq's 2004 album Ray Ray, "Chic" and "I Want You Back".
Though Moses has not released a studio album in several years, she can be found touring and doing live shows on a regular basis.
From March to November 2010 Moses was a spokesmodel on the Lady Hennessy Tour.

In addition, Moses continued to release underground, all-original mixtapes for her fans to enjoy while she awaited a new label deal that was necessitated by the Chapter 11 bankruptcy filed by the now defunct TVT Records in 2008.
On March 25, 2011, it was announced that Moses had signed to rapper Rick Ross' Maybach Music Group via Warner Bros. Records as its first female artist.
